# Project-wide Cursor AI Rules

## General
- Use TypeScript for both frontend and backend
- Follow airbnb style guide for JavaScript/TypeScript
- Use async/await for asynchronous operations
- Implement proper error handling in all async functions

## Frontend (Vue.js)
- Use Composition API for new components
- Implement lazy loading for routes
- Use Vuex for state management
- Refer to @.cursor/rules/vue.mdc for detailed Vue.js rules

## Backend (Express.js)
- Use dependency injection for services
- Implement proper input validation for all API endpoints
- Use environment variables for configuration
- Refer to @.cursor/rules/express.mdc for detailed Express.js rules

## TypeScript
- Refer to @.cursor/rules/typescript.mdc for TypeScript-specific rules
